title: AFL 2015: Carlton v North Melbourne, Gold Coast v West Coast, Round 18 live coverage | The
text:
CARLTON hosts North Melbourne at Etihad Stadium with North’s finals chances well and truly on the line.
Brad Scott's team start the match outside the eight, but can move back into the finals positions with a victory over the Blues.
IN Saturday night’s coinciding fixture, West Coast travels to Metricon Stadium to face Gold Coast hoping to move two games clear of Hawthorn inside the top two.
FOR FULL LIVE HQ COVERAGE WITH SUPERCOACH SCORES, TAP ON THE SCORE CENTRE ABOVE OR HERE IF YOU ARE ON A MOBILE DEVICE
SYDNEY put a difficult week behind them when they accounted for Adelaide by 52 points at the SCG.
Without star veteran Adam Goodes, the Swans were led by an ex-Crow in Kurt Tippett, who kicked three goals in the first quarter to set up the win.
EARLIER, Melbourne recorded an impressive win over Collingwood at the MCG to likely end the Pies’ finals hopes.
It was the Magpies’ sixth consecutive loss, placing them at 8-9 for the season so far, as the Demons prevailed by 37 points.
Bernie Vince was the star for Melbourne with three goals, while Jesse Hogan also bagged three.
AT Simonds Stadium, Josh Walker helped Geelong to a big win over the Brisbane Lions.
Walker booted five goals to help the Cats to a 56-point win over the Lions, with Josh Caddy (26 disposals and one goal), Steve Motlop (29 and one) and Joel Selwood (27 and two) continuing their outstanding recent form.
Today’s matches (all times AEST):
1.45pm: Geelong v Brisbane Lions at Simonds Stadium
2.10pm: Collingwood v Melbourne at MCG
4.35pm: Sydney Swans v Adelaide at SCG
7.20pm: Carlton v North Melbourne at Etihad Stadium
7.20pm: Gold Coast Suns v West Coast Eagles at Metricon Stadium
